timeline.bodyText:
I did not like in both versions that the exception from the setInProcessEnvironmentClass is not shown if it reaches this catch block. I looked into it and think we can work with addSuppressed.
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            try {
                throw new ReflectiveOperationException("First try");
            } catch (ReflectiveOperationException e) {
                try {
                    throw new ReflectiveOperationException("Second try");
                } catch (ReflectiveOperationException ex) {
                    ex.addSuppressed(e);
                    throw new RuntimeException("all", ex);
                }
            }
        } catch (RuntimeException runtimeE)
        {
            runtimeE.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

Output:
java.lang.RuntimeException: all
	at org.junitpioneer.Test.main(Test.java:14)
Caused by: java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException: Second try
	at org.junitpioneer.Test.main(Test.java:11)
	Suppressed: java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException: First try
		at org.junitpioneer.Test.main(Test.java:8)

